{
  "stem": "9665.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We had to eat eggs because they all wanted to pay us back.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Whatever my father earned, because in Holland you don't get your wages every week like in Australia, but once a month.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It's always in five, six, or seven days, our money was gone.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Right?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Also, the men who did our washing, right, they also needed money.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So we had quite a number of people, but I think that was the whole economy in Scheveningen, and probably Holland, that you took it from-- one-- in one hand, you gave it out in the other hand, right?",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "That's how it was.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And all together, we were what you call the [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were not poor.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were not rich.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We didn't have a car.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We had bicycles.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I went to school with a bicycle, right, from Scheveningen to the Hague, which everybody did in Holland.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was nothing unusual.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I can't say that-- you asked me that question, there's anything else towards this.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "What I forgot to tell you, Shirley, is that I left school in 1937 and I joined my father, working with him in the hosiery business.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The hosiery business was we imported from Germany, we sold it in Holland.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In 1939-- and my father had a partner by the name of [INAUDIBLE], which also from Poland, and we couldn't take it that the man really didn't give us the right wage.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So one day, as he sacked everybody every four or six weeks for the sake that we shouldn't come for an increase, we left him in 1938 or '39.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I think in 1939.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We left him from when we had our usual notice, which went on every few weeks.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
